It is loaded with numerous features and is a joy to ride in on even in rough waters. This high freeboard Crownline cruiser has a lot to offer when it comes to cabin accommodations. Built on a beamy modified V-hull of solid fiberglass construction, the mid-cabin floor plan is arranged with a canted forward berth coupled with an L-shaped dinette/lounge across from the galley and a spacious head compartment. Privacy curtains separate the sleeping areas from the main cabin, and four opening ports and three deck hatches allow for plenty of cabin ventilation.
